  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who has shown remorse by partially repaying the embezzled funds. While the breach of trust is significant, a 10-year sentence suggested by the spectator is disproportionate to the crime of $25,000. Considering the lack of prior record and the restoration of a portion of the funds, a sentence of 6 months is sufficient for deterrence and rehabilitation without being excessively punitive.",
  "verdict": 6
